[H2] Background | When a mechanic syncs form field data, the server responds with which fields were accepted and which were rejected (already filled earlier by another mechanic — First Write Wins). The mobile client must surface this to the mechanic clearly, without treating it as an error. | [H2] Server response structure | {
  "accepted": ["fieldId1", "fieldId3"],
  "rejected": [
    { "fieldId": "fieldId2", "reason": "already_written_by_other", "writtenBy": "Mechanic A" }
  ]
} | [H2] UX behavior | - Sync is considered SUCCESSFUL even if some fields are rejected — no error state. | - If rejected list is non-empty: show a dismissible info banner/snackbar. | - Message format: "Sync successful. {N} field(s) were not saved as they were already filled earlier by {mechanic name(s)}." | - Rejected fields are visually reverted on screen to the value from the server (the winning value). | - Mechanic does not need to take any action — this is informational only. | [H2] Acceptance Criteria | - After sync, if rejected list is empty: no notification shown. | - After sync, if rejected list is non-empty: info banner shown with correct count and mechanic name(s). | - Rejected field values are replaced on screen with the server-winning value. | - Sync is not shown as failed or errored when rejections exist. | - Banner is dismissible by the mechanic. | - Widget test: rejected fields trigger banner; empty rejected list shows no banner.

[H2] Service | Services.iAMS.MaintenanceExec | [H2] Changes | After the schema change (IAMS30-4338), update all Dapper queries that read or write TaskPersonalizedLog: | [H3] INSERT (session creation) | Add all 6 new columns to INSERT parameter bindings. Values must be supplied by the caller (from API request body): | INSERT INTO dbo.TaskPersonalizedLog
  (..., ShiftName, UserFullName, SiteCode, SiteName, SectionId, SectionName)
VALUES
  (..., @ShiftName, @UserFullName, @SiteCode, @SiteName, @SectionId, @SectionName) | [H3] SELECT (reads) | - Add all 6 columns to SELECT column lists. | - Add all 6 fields to the DTO/entity class mapping (TaskPersonalizedLog DTO or equivalent). | [H3] UPDATE (auto-close / Finish tap) | - All 6 new columns must NOT appear in UPDATE statements — they are immutable after creation. | - UPDATE only sets EndDate (and ModifiedAt, ModifiedBy). | [H2] DTO / Entity Update | public class TaskPersonalizedLogDto {
  // existing fields...
