} | [H2] Verification | - Run existing tests to confirm no regressions. | - Add integration test: create session with all 6 fields populated, read back and assert values match. | - Assert that UPDATE (auto-close) does not overwrite any of the 6 snapshot columns.

[H2] Background | Before the Planner submits a plan with a form package, the system must show a confirmation popup that: (1) displays all selected forms, and (2) checks whether each form is still available in maintenance-strategy. If any form is unavailable, the Confirm button is disabled until the Planner removes that form or re-activates it in Form Builder. This prevents plans from being submitted with broken form references — which would cause mechanics to see "Form not available" errors in the field. | [H2] Context: when this popup appears | Triggered when the Planner clicks the primary Submit / Create button after completing the Choose Form step (Step 2). This replaces or extends the existing submit confirmation (if any). | [H2] Popup Content | - Title: "Confirm Plan Submission" | - Body: list of all selected forms, each showing: form name, Mandatory/Optional badge, availability status. | - Availability status per form: checking (loading), Available (green), Not Available (red + reason). | - Footer: Cancel button (always enabled) + Confirm button (enabled only when all forms are Available). | [H2] Form Availability Rules | A form is considered NOT AVAILABLE if any of the following is true: | - Not found in maintenance-strategy at all (hard deleted). | - IsActive = 0 (deactivated). | - Status = Archived. | If the Planner has no forms selected (empty package), skip the availability check — Confirm button is enabled immediately. | [H2] API call for availability check | GET /api/maintenance-strategy/forms/availability?formIds=uuid1,uuid2,...

Response:
[
  { "formId": "uuid1", "isAvailable": true },
  { "formId": "uuid2", "isAvailable": false, "reason": "Form is archived" }
] | Note: this API endpoint may need to be created. Coordinate with BE if not yet available. | [H2] UX Flow | - 1. Planner clicks Submit/Create. | - 2. Popup opens showing form list with "checking..." status per form. | - 3. FE calls availability check API. | - 4. Each form updates to Available or Not Available. | - 5. If all available: Confirm enabled. Planner clicks Confirm -> existing create plan API called. | - 6. If any not available: Confirm stays disabled. Planner must go back and remove the unavailable form(s) from the package. | [H2] Acceptance Criteria | - Confirmation popup appears when Planner clicks Submit after Choose Form step. | - All selected forms are listed with their Mandatory/Optional badge. | - Availability check API is called for all forms in the list. | - Forms that are unavailable show a red Not Available status with reason. | - Confirm button is disabled if any form is Not Available. | - Confirm button is enabled when all forms are Available (or no forms selected). | - Clicking Confirm proceeds with the existing create plan API call (IAMS30-4272 base scope). | - Clicking Cancel closes the popup without submitting.

[H2] Context | DTO untuk plan submit menggunakan FormCode (bukan FormId + Version). Planner tidak peduli versi — versi aktif di-resolve oleh consumer di maintenance-execution saat event diproses. | [H2] Command / DTO — dplan side | public class SubmitPlanCommand {
  public Guid PlanId { get; set; }
  // ... existing fields ...
  public List<PlanFormItem> PlanForms { get; set; } = new();
}

public class PlanFormItem {
  public string FormCode { get; set; }   // identitas form lintas versi
  public bool IsMandatory { get; set; }  // ditentukan Planner
}

// Outbox event payload
public class PlanSubmittedEvent {
  public Guid PlanId { get; set; }
  public string PlanName { get; set; }
  public DateTime ProjectStart { get; set; }
  public string SiteId { get; set; }
  public string MaintenanceCategoryCode { get; set; }
  public string MaintenanceCategoryName { get; set; }
  public string AssetNumber { get; set; }
  public List<PlanFormEventItem> PlanForms { get; set; }
}

public class PlanFormEventItem {
  public string FormCode { get; set; }
  public bool IsMandatory { get; set; }
} | [H2] Acceptance Criteria | - DTO menggunakan FormCode + IsMandatory (bukan FormId + FormName + Version). | - PlanSubmittedEvent payload sesuai struktur di atas. | - Unit test: DTO mapping dan event payload serialization.

[H2] Konteks penting | Exponential backoff TIDAK tersedia native di Azure Service Bus Standard tier. Perlu konfirmasi tier sebelum implementasi. | [H2] Langkah 1: Konfirmasi tier | - Cek Azure portal: tier aktif di dev, staging, dan production. | - Premium tier: gunakan built-in retry dengan exponential backoff. | - Standard tier: implementasi workaround via scheduled re-enqueue (lihat kode di bawah). | - Dokumentasikan keputusan di PR. | [H2] Target retry policy | Parameter || Value | Max Delivery Count || 5 | Lock Duration || 5 menit | Backoff || Exponential: 30s, 1m, 2m, 4m | DLQ || Setelah attempt ke-5, alert ke ops | [H2] Workaround Standard tier: scheduled re-enqueue | var delays = new[] { 30, 60, 120, 240 }; // detik
int deliveryCount = args.Message.DeliveryCount;
if (deliveryCount < delays.Length) {
  var delay = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(delays[deliveryCount - 1]);
  await sender.ScheduleMessageAsync(args.Message.Clone(),
    DateTimeOffset.UtcNow + delay);
  await args.CompleteMessageAsync(args.Message);
} else {
  await args.DeadLetterMessageAsync(args.Message, "MaxRetriesExceeded");
} | [H2] Acceptance Criteria | - Tier Service Bus terdokumentasi di PR. | - Topic dan subscription PlanSubmitted terbuat di semua environment. | - Retry policy diterapkan (Max 5, Lock 5 menit, exponential via native atau workaround). | - Pesan gagal 5x masuk DLQ. | - Alert terkonfigurasi ketika DLQ message count > 0.

